Our Leadership
Meet our Leaders
 






 




There’s No Right Way To Do A Wrong Thing
Whirlpool Corporation maintains our successful perspective by employing and empowering 100,000 unique points of view. On the front lines are leaders who create momentum and competitive advantages so our products excite consumers and employees alike.  From the beginning, Whirlpool has been committed to upholding our values of mutual Respect, Integrity, Diversity and Inclusion, Teamwork and the Spirit of Winning. We fulfill our obligation to earn and maintain the trust of stakeholders, employees and the community by adhering to and setting the highest values and standards possible. These standards also steer our leadership teams to recruit and mentor our global and diverse workforce by modeling high standards of behavior.

 
 
 




 



Board of Directors
Whirlpool Corporation is governed by a board of directors comprised of 13 members, 11 of whom are independent. The board’s principles and processes guide the board, which includes internal annual reviews of board practices.
The Executive Committee
This 10-member senior management group is comprised of the chairman and chief executive officer (CEO), Jeff Fettig, and leadership from all of the company’s major functions and regions. It exists to manage the operations of the company in accordance with the company’s high ethical and professional standards, while providing the operational oversight to enable the company to meet our business objectives.


 
 
 
 
 
 



